The paper deals with graph theory and algorithms, which are typically covered in the arXiv CS sub-categories of Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Geometry (cs.CG), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), and Machine Learning (cs.LG). However, since the focus of the paper is on treewidth and its parameterization, the most likely categories are cs.DM and cs.DS, which are specifically concerned with discrete mathematics and data structures/algorithms, respectively. The other categories are also relevant due to the algorithmic and computational aspects of the paper.
